Perfume Project

Ryan Cartularo and Victoria Fuller

10/26/2021

Brief Introduction:

Our project is to explore the Perfume dataset created by Sagi Keren, which is available here: https://www.kaggle.com/sagikeren88/fragrances-and-perfumes. Namely the goal is to look at the trends that fragrances have experienced through the years and decades.

Our dataset is a collection of the data curated on the website Fragrantica.com, which is the most popular website for perfume information by a wide margin. It collects user reviews of individual fragrances from the mid 1700s to now and also polls users about what situations those fragrances are most suited for (day, night, fall, summer, …etc). The other big bit of information it stores is the notes used in each fragrance.

perfume <- perfume %>%
  select(-c('longevity_poor','longevity_weak','longevity_moderate','longevity_long','longevity_very_long', 'sillage_soft', 'sillage_moderate','sillage_heavy','sillage_enormous','clslove_female25under','clslove_male25under','clslove_female25older','clslove_male25older','clslike_female25under','clslike_male25under','clslike_female25older','clslike_male25older','clsdislike_female25under','clsdislike_male25under','clsdislike_female25older','clsdislike_male25older','clswinter_female25under','clswinter_male25under','clswinter_female25older','clswinter_male25older','clsspring_female25under','clsspring_male25under','clsspring_female25older','clsspring_male25older','clssummer_female25under','clssummer_male25under','clssummer_female25older','clssummer_male25older','clsautumn_female25under','clsautumn_male25under','clsautumn_female25older','clsautumn_male25older','clsday_female25under','clsday_male25under','clsday_female25older','clsday_male25older','clsnight_female25under','clsnight_male25under','clsnight_female25older','clsnight_male25older')) %>%
  mutate_at(vars(title, accords, notes_1,notes_2,notes_3,notes_4,notes_5,notes_6,notes_7,notes_8,notes_9,
                 notes_10,notes_11,notes_12,notes_13,notes_14,notes_15,notes_16,notes_17,notes_18,notes_19 , notes_20), ~ as.factor(.)) %>%
  filter(rating_score > 0) %>%
  filter(votes > 0) %>%
  filter(date < 2022) %>%
  filter(date > 1759) %>%
  mutate(popularity = (rating_score * votes))

Columns Explained

…1:

The Company That Produced The Perfume

title:

The Name of The Individual Perfume

date:

The Year The Perfume Was First Produced

accords:

The Main categories that the perfume is filling (like “fruity” or “spicy”), can be thought of as a combination of notes

rating_score:

A scale of 1-5 on how user’s of Fragrantica.com judge the quality of the perfume to be

votes:

How many people have voted on this fragrance (Note: this only relates to the rating_score column)

clslove:

Percentage of users who ‘love’ this fragrance

clslike:

Percentage of users who ‘like’ this fragrance

clsdislike:

Percentage of users who ‘dislike’ this fragrance

clswinter:

Percentage of users who think this fragrance is better in the winter

clsspring:

Percentage of users who think this fragrance is better in the spring

clssummer:

Percentage of users who think this fragrance is better in the summer

clsautumn:

Percentage of users who think this fragrance is better in the fall

clscold:

of users who think this fragrance is better in cold weather

clshot:

Percentage of users who think this fragrance is better in hot weather

clsday:

Percentage of users who think this fragrance is better suited for daytime use

clsnight:

Percentage of users who think this fragrance is better suited for nighttime use

Ihaveit:

Number of users who claim to own this fragrance

Ihadit:

Number of users who claim to have used to own the fragrance

Iwantit:

number of users who want the fragrance

notes_1…notes_20:

The individual elements you are supposed to be able to smell in a fragrance in descending power (so the concentration of a note will be stronger in notes_1 than notes_20)

gender:

The gender that the fragrance is marketed towards

popularity:

A column that we created who is the product of votes & rating_score. This is our output because it is a reasonably good predictor of the quality of a fragrance

Our Summary Statistics

Our Summaries and Standard Deviations Of The Basic Important Columns

These summary statistics are for the columns that we created. At the moment, the only new column we think necessary is the creation of a “popularity” column that is the product of the rating_score and votes columns. We felt this was a more accurate predictor of the overall quality of a perfume since there are several perfumes with perfect ratings of ‘5’ but only one or two votes.

summary(perfume$popularity)
##    Min. 1st Qu.  Median    Mean 3rd Qu.    Max. 
##     1.0    36.0   118.8  1283.6   833.5 35242.2
sd(perfume$popularity)
## [1] 3330.843

Histogram of date

We have adjusted the bins of the two graphs below so that the first graph displays a bar for each individual year of perfume history, which we judge to start in 1760 with The House of Creed’s: ‘Royal Service’. The second graph displays a bar for each decade of perfume history

ggplot(tibble(x=perfume$date)) + geom_histogram(aes(x=x), bins=261)

ggplot(tibble(x=perfume$date)) + geom_histogram(aes(x=x), bins=26)

Bar Plot of date vs popularity

ggplot(perfume) + geom_col(aes(x=date,y=popularity))

Creating A Basic Model

model.complete <- lm(popularity ~ notes_1 + notes_2 + notes_3 + notes_4 + notes_5 + notes_6 + notes_7 + notes_8 + notes_9 + notes_10 + notes_11 + notes_12 + notes_13 + notes_14 + notes_15 + notes_16 + notes_17 + notes_18 + notes_19 + notes_20, perfume)

Using Stepwise Regression To Make Our Final Model For The Popularity Of All Perfume

Making a Basic Model For Each Important Decade Of Perfumery

perfume70 <- perfumeuse %>%
  select(-c('longevity_poor','longevity_weak','longevity_moderate','longevity_long','longevity_very_long', 'sillage_soft', 'sillage_moderate','sillage_heavy','sillage_enormous','clslove_female25under','clslove_male25under','clslove_female25older','clslove_male25older','clslike_female25under','clslike_male25under','clslike_female25older','clslike_male25older','clsdislike_female25under','clsdislike_male25under','clsdislike_female25older','clsdislike_male25older','clswinter_female25under','clswinter_male25under','clswinter_female25older','clswinter_male25older','clsspring_female25under','clsspring_male25under','clsspring_female25older','clsspring_male25older','clssummer_female25under','clssummer_male25under','clssummer_female25older','clssummer_male25older','clsautumn_female25under','clsautumn_male25under','clsautumn_female25older','clsautumn_male25older','clsday_female25under','clsday_male25under','clsday_female25older','clsday_male25older','clsnight_female25under','clsnight_male25under','clsnight_female25older','clsnight_male25older')) %>%
  mutate_at(vars(title, accords, notes_1,notes_2,notes_3,notes_4,notes_5,notes_6,notes_7,notes_8,notes_9,
                 notes_10,notes_11,notes_12,notes_13,notes_14,notes_15,notes_16,notes_17,notes_18,notes_19 , notes_20), ~ as.factor(.)) %>%
  filter(rating_score > 0) %>%
  filter(votes > 0) %>%
  filter(date < 1980) %>%
  filter(date > 1970) %>%
  mutate(popularity70 = (rating_score * votes))

Successful Notes: Coriander, Lavender, Black Tea, Cardamom, Musk

Unsuccessful Notes: Kephalis, Opoponax, Sandalwood, Oud, Oakmoss

Ending Notes:

We have filtered our date to only include entries that are between 1760 and 2021 because this dataset is simply so large that there is a lot of junk data with incorrect values in it, like dates with a value of 9000.

Similarly we also have filtered out entries with 0 votes or 0 rating_score because this means that those perfumes have not been reviewed at all and thus only serve to skew our results(in a large way since a very large number of the entries have a rating_score of 0).
